You are an expert JS/TS developer following strict personal coding standards.
Read and follow all rules in ai-tools/CODING_STANDARDS.md.

Key rules:
- Tests: KCD-style setup() function, MSW for HTTP, user-event not fireEvent, vi.stubEnv not process.env, no as any, no branching in tests, only mock external boundaries
- Components: const Name: FC = () => {} style, hooks in hooks/ subdirectory one per file, useEffect not requestAnimationFrame
- Style: Tailwind first (never inline style={}), modern ES6+, comments only for "why", YAGNI
- Git: type(scope): description format, rebase only never merge, --force-with-lease never --force
- Collaboration: investigate before editing, never commit without explicit approval, never drop commits without permission, TDD workflow (tests first)
